Class MORCone

    public class MORCone
extends MOROrientable
implements Semantics.Cone<MORDescriptor>
    The java/semantic mapper for a Cone, based on aMOR OWL references.

    It implements a two way mapping interface between this java structure and a semantic individual. It extends MOROrientable so, it apply its inherited part of the semantic description of an object. Nevertheless, it adds also the definition of the radius, height and the coordinate of the apex of a cone. Such a procedure is still based on OWL data properties that reflect the fields of Semantics.Cone, where the ontology interface is based on the MORDescriptor class.

      • MORCone

        public MORCone(java.lang.String ontologyName,
               long id)
        Construct this class with all invalidate fields. For instance, initially readSemantics() should be called.
        It is based on MOROrientable.MOROrientable(String, long) and the apex is created as MOR3DArray.MOR3DArray(), where its property names is set, for X, Y and Z, as; APEX_COORDINATE_X_DATA_PROPERTY_NAME, APEX_COORDINATE_Y_DATA_PROPERTY_NAME, and APEX_COORDINATE_Z_DATA_PROPERTY_NAME respectively. Finally, the radius and height of the cone is set to null.
        Parameters:
        ontologyName - the name to an instantiated OWLReferences that will describe this cone semantically.
        id - the unique identifier of this cone.

      • MORCone

        public MORCone(java.lang.String ontologyName,
               long id,
               MOR3DArray centroid,
               MOR3DArray axis,
               java.lang.Double radius,
               java.lang.Double height,
               MOR3DArray apex)
        Construct this class by specifying all its fields. For instance, initially writeSemantics() should be called.
        It is based on MOROrientable.MOROrientable(String, long, MOR3DArray, MOR3DArray), where the input apex may already contains some property names (see MOR3DArray.hasXproperty(), MOR3DArray.hasYproperty() and MOR3DArray.hasZproperty()). If not, those are set as; APEX_COORDINATE_X_DATA_PROPERTY_NAME, APEX_COORDINATE_Y_DATA_PROPERTY_NAME, and APEX_COORDINATE_Z_DATA_PROPERTY_NAME.
        Parameters:
        ontologyName - the name to an instantiated OWLReferences that will describe this cone semantically.
        id - the unique identifier of this cone.
        centroid - the coordinates of the center of mass of this cone.
        axis - the value of a vector aligned to the principal axis of this cone.
        radius - the radius of this cone.
        height - the height of this cone.
        apex - the coordinate of the apex of this cone.

      • writeSemantics

        public Semantics.WritingState writeSemantics()
        Synchronise the java representation of this Cone with the ontology and return the process state.

        It calls MOROrientable.writeSemantics() and than, if the state of the operation MappingState#isOK(), it uses MORDescriptor.writeLiteral(String, OWLDataProperty, OWLLiteral) to write the radius, and height, described by this class (called with parameter as: getRadiusProperty(), getRadiusLiteral() and getHeightProperty(), getHeightLiteral() respectively). Finally, if the state of the operation is still MappingState#isOK(), it uses MOR3DArray.writeSemantics(MORDescriptor) to write the apex of this cone. Those writing process generate more writing states, that are merged in a single outcome based on: Semantics.WritingState#merge(WritingState).

        Specified by:
        writeSemantics in interface Semantics
        Overrides:
        writeSemantics in class MOROrientable
        Returns:
        the state of this writing process.
        See Also:
        Primitive#writeSemantics(), MOR3DArray.writeSemantics(MORDescriptor), WritingState

      • readSemantics

        public Semantics.ReadingState readSemantics()
        Synchronise the ontology representation of a Cone object with this java structure and return the process state.

        It calls MOROrientable.readSemantics() and than, if the state of the operation MappingState#isOK(), it uses MORDescriptor.readLiteral(String, OWLDataProperty, OWLLiteral) to read the radius, and height, from the ontology (called with parameter as: getRadiusProperty(), getRadiusLiteral() and getHeightProperty(), getHeightLiteral() respectively). Finally, if the state of the operation is still MappingState#isOK(), it uses MOR3DArray.readSemantics(MORDescriptor) to red the apex of this cone. Those reading process generate more reading states, that are merged in a single outcome based on: Semantics.WritingState#merge(WritingState).

        Specified by:
        readSemantics in interface Semantics
        Overrides:
        readSemantics in class MOROrientable
        Returns:
        the state of this reading process.
        See Also:
        Primitive#readSemantics(), MOR3DArray.readSemantics(MORDescriptor), ReadingState
